  "8": {
    "chapterId": 8,
    "title": "副詞",
    "page": 115,
    "subLessons": [
      {
        "id": "8-1",
        "title": "頻率副詞",
        "teaching": {
          "explanation": "<b>頻率副詞代表多常發生</b><br>always（100%）、usually（75%）、often（65%）、sometimes（50%）、seldom/rarely（10%）、never（0%），另外ever（曾經，用於疑問句）、hardly（幾乎不）。<br><br><b>放在句子的哪個位置</b><br>① be動詞之後：She is always happy at school.<br>② 一般動詞之前：Mr. Wang always likes to eat out.<br>③ 助動詞與一般動詞之間：He can never play baseball.<br>④ sometimes可放句首或句尾：Sometimes Ted rides a bike to school. = Ted rides a bike to school sometimes.<br>⑤ often也可放句尾：David eats hamburgers for lunch often.<br>⑥ 程度副詞（so/too/very/quite）+often，一定放句尾：Mom cooks dinner at home very often.<br><br><b>ever跟祈使句的特殊規則</b><br>① ever只能用於疑問句、否定句，或現在完成式的形容詞子句，不能用在一般肯定句：Do you ever go to the beach?　This is the best place I have ever seen.<br>② 祈使句中，always/never放句首表示「永遠」「絕不」：Always be a good student. / Never talk in class.<br><br><b>否定意味的頻率副詞怎麼連接</b><br>seldom、hardly、never本身已經是否定，句中不必再加not。同一主詞若要連接兩個都帶否定意味的頻率副詞，要用and，不能用but：He never eats beef and seldom eats pork.（不能用but，因為兩者語氣一致，都是否定）<br><br><b>How often的答法</b><br>可以用頻率副詞回答，也可以用「次數+固定時間」回答：once a week（一週一次）、twice a day（一天兩次）、every other day（每隔一天）、twice every five weeks（每五週兩次）。<br><br><b>正確觀念存取區</b><br>① not always「並非總是」是部分否定，意思接近sometimes，跟always not「總是不」意思完全不同。<br>② 頻率副詞總和不可超過100%：He sometimes goes there, but usually comes here.（sometimes+usually超過100%，必須用but轉折）；但He sometimes goes there and sometimes comes here.（兩個sometimes加起來不超過100%，可以用and）。",
          "examples": [
            {
              "en": "My grandfather always takes a walk after dinner.",
              "zh": "我爺爺晚餐後總是會去散步。"
            },
