      {
        "id": "8-3",
        "title": "程度副詞",
        "teaching": {
          "explanation": "<b>修飾形容詞或副詞：放在前面</b><br>very、too、so、quite、really、pretty、still、enough（例外）都放在被修飾的形容詞或副詞前面：The news is really exciting. / Linda walked home so lazily.<br><br><b>such vs so 最容易搞混</b><br>such是形容詞，修飾後面的名詞；so是程度副詞，修飾後面的形容詞或副詞。兩者可以互相改寫：It is so tall a tree. = It is such a tall tree.（這棵樹真高。）<br><br><b>修飾動詞的程度副詞</b><br>放動詞前：really、almost、only、also、still：I also have to go to school on holidays.<br>放句尾：so much、very much、a lot、a little：This book helps me a lot.<br><br><b>enough比較特別</b><br>當形容詞修飾名詞時放名詞前（前位修飾）：If you don't have enough money...<br>當副詞修飾形容詞或副詞時，反而要放在後面：Jean is tall enough to be on the team. / You don't study hard enough.<br><br><b>so...that / enough to / too...to 三兄弟比較</b><br>① so+形容詞/副詞+that+完整子句「如此…以致於…」：The coffee is so strong that we can't drink it.（子句主詞、受詞都不可省略）<br>② 形容詞/副詞+enough+to V「夠…而能…」：Oscar is tall enough to join the team.<br>③ too+形容詞/副詞+to V「太…而不能…」：Tom is too lazy to get good grades.<br>④ so that（不同於so...that）表示「目的」，等於in order to：He gets up early so that he can catch the bus. = He gets up early to catch the bus.<br><br><b>enough to／too...to 受詞什麼時候該省略</b><br>當不定詞後面的受詞其實就是句子主詞本身時，這個受詞必須省略：The soup is too hot to drink.（不能說to drink it，因為it其實就是the soup，重複了）；但如果不定詞的受詞跟主詞是不同對象，就要留著：He is old enough to do it.（it跟he是不同對象，要保留）",
          "examples": [
            {
              "en": "This math problem is quite difficult for me.",
              "zh": "這道數學題對我來說相當困難。"
            },
            {
              "en": "It was such an exciting game that everyone cheered loudly.",
              "zh": "那場比賽如此刺激，以致於大家都大聲歡呼。"
            },
            {
              "en": "I also enjoy painting in my free time.",
              "zh": "我空閒時也喜歡畫畫。"
            },
            {
              "en": "This backpack helped me a lot during the trip.",
              "zh": "這個背包在旅途中幫了我很大的忙。"
            },
            {
              "en": "Do you have enough time to finish the report?",
              "zh": "你有足夠的時間完成這份報告嗎？"
            },
            {
              "en": "The soup was too salty to drink.",
              "zh": "這碗湯太鹹了，沒辦法喝。"
            },
            {
              "en": "She is smart enough to solve the puzzle by herself.",
              "zh": "她夠聰明可以自己解開這個謎題。"
            },
            {
              "en": "He studies hard so that he can pass the exam.",
              "zh": "他很用功讀書，好讓他可以通過考試。"
            },
            {
              "en": "The bag is so heavy that I can't carry it alone.",
              "zh": "這個袋子這麼重，我沒辦法自己搬。"
            },
            {
              "en": "I'm still waiting for her reply.",
              "zh": "我還在等她的回覆。"
            }
          ]
        },
