  "9": {
    "chapterId": 9,
    "title": "形容詞與副詞的級",
    "page": 129,
    "subLessons": [
      {
        "id": "9-1",
        "title": "形容詞的比較級",
        "teaching": {
          "explanation": "<b>什麼時候用比較級</b><br>兩者做比較時使用，句中通常會出現than。只要句中有than，一定是比較級（不管句子裡有多少人事物）。<br><br><b>規則變化</b><br>單音節字尾加er：fast→faster；字尾e加r：nice→nicer；短母音+子音重複字尾：big→bigger；子音+y去y加ier：happy→happier；兩音節以上前面加more/less：comfortable→more comfortable。<br><br><b>不規則變化</b><br>good/well→better；bad/ill→worse；many/much→more；little→less（注意：few→fewer，few本身已是「少」的意思，比較級用fewer不是lesser）。<br><br><b>基本句構</b><br>A+be+比較級+than+B(+be)：He is taller than his father (is).<br><br><b>「其他」的概念要注意</b><br>如果主詞跟「同一個範圍」的人事物做比較，而主詞本身也屬於這個範圍，就要用「其他」的概念，把主詞排除在外，不然會自己跟自己比。錯誤：I am smarter than the students in my class.（我也是班上學生之一，等於拿自己跟包含自己的一群人比）。正確：I am smarter than all the other students in my class.／than any other student in my class.／than everyone else.<br><br><b>劣等比較（比較不…）</b><br>用less+原級+than，表示比較差：John is less smart than Kim. = Kim is smarter than John.<br><br><b>強調比較的差距</b><br>much、far、a lot、even（多了很多）；a little、a bit（一點點）；也可以寫出具體數字：John is five years older than I. / Tom is three times heavier than you.（是你的三倍重）。注意：程度副詞too、so、very、quite不能修飾比較級，只能修飾原級。<br><br><b>同類比較</b><br>than前後比較的對象詞性、邏輯範圍要一致：My hair is longer than your hair.（不能說longer than your car，頭髮不能跟車子比長度）。<br><br><b>特殊比較級要記住</b><br>old→older（年紀較老）/elder（較年長，通常指家人排行）；far→farther（距離更遠）/further（程度上更進一步）；late→later（時間較晚）/latter（次序較後）。",
          "examples": [
            {
              "en": "This backpack is heavier than that one.",
              "zh": "這個背包比那個重。"
            },
            {
              "en": "My brother is taller than all the other boys in his class.",
              "zh": "我哥哥比他班上所有其他男生都高。"
            },
            {
              "en": "This exam was much easier than the last one.",
              "zh": "這次考試比上次簡單多了。"
            },
            {
              "en": "She is three years younger than her sister.",
              "zh": "她比她姐姐小三歲。"
            },
            {
              "en": "The blue shirt is less expensive than the red one.",
              "zh": "藍色的襯衫比紅色的便宜。"
            },
            {
              "en": "No other player on the team runs faster than Kevin.",
              "zh": "隊上沒有其他球員跑得比Kevin快。"
            },
            {
              "en": "This coffee tastes better than the one I made yesterday.",
              "zh": "這杯咖啡比我昨天泡的還好喝。"
            },
            {
              "en": "His new phone is twice as expensive as mine.",
              "zh": "他的新手機是我的兩倍貴。"
            },
            {
              "en": "The weather today is far colder than yesterday.",
              "zh": "今天的天氣比昨天冷多了。"
            },
            {
              "en": "Reading is more relaxing to me than watching TV.",
              "zh": "對我來說，閱讀比看電視更放鬆。"
            }
          ]
        },
        "quiz": {
          "mc": [
            {
              "sentence": "This lake is ___ than that one.",
              "options": [
                "deep",
                "deeper",
                "the deepest",
                "more deep"
              ],
              "answer": 1,
              "explanation": "單音節形容詞deep的比較級加er，變成deeper。",
              "target_grammar": "形容詞比較級",
              "optionsZh": [
                "（原級，句中有than需用比較級）",
                "（正確，單音節加er）",
                "（最高級用法，此處只比較兩者）",
                "（單音節不用more，直接加er）"
              ]
            },
            {
              "sentence": "Lucy is smarter than ___ in her class.",
              "options": [
                "everyone",
                "everyone else",
                "the students",
                "all students"
              ],
              "answer": 1,
              "explanation": "Lucy本身也是班上學生之一，要用「其他」的概念everyone else排除自己。",
              "target_grammar": "形容詞比較級",
              "optionsZh": [
                "（沒有排除Lucy自己，會產生矛盾）",
                "（正確，everyone else排除主詞自己）",
                "（沒有排除Lucy自己，會自相矛盾）",
                "（沒有排除Lucy自己，會自相矛盾）"
              ]
            },
            {
              "sentence": "This shirt is ___ than that one, so I'll buy the other one instead.",
              "options": [
                "less nice",
                "more less nice",
                "less nicer",
                "nicer less"
              ],
              "answer": 0,
              "explanation": "劣等比較用less+原級，不可用less再加比較級nicer（重複比較）。",
              "target_grammar": "形容詞比較級",
