      {
        "id": "18-3",
        "title": "關係副詞",
        "teaching": {
          "explanation": "<b>什麼是關係副詞</b><br>若形容詞子句已經是一個「完整的句子」（不缺主詞也不缺受詞），就不能再用關係代名詞，而要用「<b>關係副詞</b>」來連接。關係副詞相當於「介系詞 ＋ which（關代）」，因為它代替的是「副詞（片語）」，不是名詞。<br>核心觀念：關代代替的是「名詞（主詞／受詞）」；關係副詞代替的是「副詞（表地點、時間、原因、方法）」。<br><br><b>一、where（代替地點）＝ in / on / at which</b><br>先行詞為「地方」，且形容詞子句已完整時，用 where。<br>‧ I still remember the place <b>(where)</b> we lived for years.<br>＝ I still remember the place <b>in which</b> we lived for years.<br>‧ This is the house <b>(where)</b> John stayed last night.＝ …the house <b>in which</b> John stayed…<br><br><b>二、when（代替時間）＝ in / on / at which</b><br>先行詞為「時間」，形容詞子句已完整時，用 when。<br>‧ Do you know the date <b>(when)</b> John and Mandy got married?＝ …the date <b>on which</b>…<br>‧ Tell me the time <b>(when)</b> we should meet.＝ …the time <b>at which</b>…<br><br><b>三、why（代替原因）＝ for which</b><br>先行詞為 the reason（原因）時用 why。<br>‧ This is the reason <b>why</b> he decided to leave us.（這就是他決定離開我們的原因。）＝ …the reason <b>for which</b>…<br><br><b>四、how（代替方法）</b><br>多數人認為 how 不算標準關係副詞。表「方法」時，the way 與 how 不可同時出現：<br>‧ ✓ This is <b>how</b> he did it.＝ This is <b>the way (in / by which)</b> he did it.<br>‧ ✗ This is <b>the way how</b> he did it.（此用法不常見，避免使用。）<br><br><b>where / when / why 皆可省略</b>（作關係副詞時）。<br><br><b>最重要的判斷法：關代 vs. 關係副詞</b><br>先看形容詞子句「缺不缺名詞」：<br>‧ 缺主詞或受詞（句子不完整）→ 用「關代」（who/which/that…）。<br>‧ 句子已完整（不缺名詞）→ 用「關係副詞」（where/when/why）。<br>例：This is the city <b>where</b> he was born.（he was born 已完整 → where）<br>對照：This is the house <b>which</b> we are going to buy.（buy 缺受詞 → which）<br><br><b>★ 易錯陷阱</b><br>並不是「先行詞是地方」就一定用 where！要看子句是否完整：<br>‧ The house <b>which</b> Mr. Brown wanted to sell was burned.（sell 缺受詞，the house 當受詞 → 用 which，不可用 where）<br>‧ I like the zoo <b>that</b> has pandas.（the zoo 當主詞 → 用 that/which，不可用 where）<br>口訣：「先行詞是地方不等於用 where；子句缺名詞就要用關代。」",
          "examples": [
            {
              "en": "This is the park where we used to play basketball after school.",
              "zh": "這就是我們以前放學後常打籃球的公園。"
            },
