      {
        "id": "18-4",
        "title": "關代限用 that 的情形",
        "teaching": {
          "explanation": "<b>觀念</b><br>在某些情況下，先行詞前面若出現特定字詞，習慣上「關代優先（傾向）用 that」，而不用 who 或 which。這是考試最愛考的重點，務必背熟。<br><br><b>情形一：先行詞被下列字詞修飾時，用 that</b><br>當先行詞前面有這些字，關代用 that：<br>‧ <b>all</b>（所有）、<b>no-／every-／any-／some-</b> 開頭的字（no one、everything、anything、something…）<br>‧ <b>the only</b>（唯一的）、<b>the very</b>（正是那個）、<b>the same</b>（相同的）<br>‧ <b>比較級／最高級</b>（如 the biggest、the first…）<br>‧ <b>序數</b>（the first、the second…）<br>例：<br>‧ Tom is the <b>first</b> boy <b>that</b> I knew in elementary school.<br>‧ <b>Any</b> student <b>that</b> is named Peter will get a special gift today.<br>‧ Have you seen the <b>most popular</b> movie <b>that</b> is about the future?<br>‧ <b>All</b> <b>that</b> you have to do is wait quietly.<br>記憶口訣：「<b>序最同唯，all 與 no/every/any/some，關代選 that</b>。」<br><br><b>情形二：先行詞為「人與動物（事物）的組合」時，用 that</b><br>當先行詞同時包含「人」和「動物／事物」，因為無法同時用 who 和 which，就用 that。<br>‧ Tom and his dog <b>that</b> played in the park got hurt this morning.<br>‧ I love my mom and her pie <b>that</b> gives me a lot of memories.<br><br><b>情形三：句子開頭為疑問詞 who、which、whom 時，用 that</b><br>為避免同一句中出現「兩個相同的字（疑問詞與關代重複）」，關代改用 that，讓句子更美觀。<br>‧ <b>Who</b> is the boy <b>that</b> you talk with on the phone every night?（避免 Who … who）<br>‧ <b>Which</b> is your ideal car <b>that</b> you want to buy?（避免 Which … which）<br><br><b>補充延伸</b><br>1. 隨著語言口語化，anyone who、someone who 等也逐漸通用，但考試時遇到 all／the only／最高級／序數等，仍以 that 為標準答案。<br>2. that 雖然萬用，但有「三不用」：① 逗號之後（非限定用法）② 介系詞之後 ③ 所有格。這三種情形絕不可用 that（詳見 18-5）。<br>3. 這裡的 that 是「關係代名詞」，別和「that 引導名詞子句」（如 I know that he is right.）搞混——關代 that 後面的子句一定缺主詞或受詞。",
          "examples": [
